HEADWORD: Horsiness
<hw>Hors"i*ness</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
condition or quality of being a horse; that which pertains to a
horse.</def> <rj><au>Tennyson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fondness for, or interest in, horses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Horsly</ent>⟦br⟧
